<p style="text-align:justify;">Having seen so much resemblance between all the nations around the Pole, let us now see the manners of those in more temperate climates.</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">"Our Road led us by a fountain where in this cold weather some women were washing &#8211; none of them were completely clothed; and one in particular had for her covering only a piece of an old blanket with two holes torn in the upper end of it, through which instead of sleeves, she put her arms.  It was too small to cover her chest, too short to reach below the waist, and it was with difficulty that by holding the lower corners in her two hands she made them meet."</p>
<p style="text-align:right;">Sutherland's Tour to Constantinople page 190.</p>
